The paper discusses one-shot neural architecture search (NAS) and its benchmarking, which are topics that are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper also discusses hyperparameter tuning and optimization, which are topics that fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.AR (Hardware Architecture).
